<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7544> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7544" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 135. In MRR 1.488-489, the invaders who were attacked by the consul should be called Ardeii and Palarii as in App. Illyr. 10 (M. G. Morgan, Athenaeum 49, 1971, 255). In MRR 1.488-489, refer also to CIL 1(2).2.635-ILS 22-ILLRP 332.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7544 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3126> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3126" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 125, 468f. ([Q. Ca]lpurnius C. [f. C. n.] Piso); Obseq. 26; Chr. 354 (Flacco et Pisone), so also Fast. Hyd., and Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 5.6.1; Cassiod.; and on Flaccus, CIL 1\n     .2.635- ILS 22; SIG(3) 688; Liv. Per. 56. Flaccus repelled an invasion of Illyria by{489} Vardaei (Liv. Per. 56; App. Illyr. 10). Piso in Hither Spain attacked Pallantia (App. Ib. 83), while Obsequens records a defeat at Numantia (26; see Schulten, Gesch. Numantia 81)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3126 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3095> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3095" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest possible date before his consulship." ;
	dprr:hasID 3095 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10095> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10095" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/31> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph? de Vardaeis. Itgenshorst no.212e (triumphus incertus). Not listed in MRR or Rich." ;
	dprr:hasID 10095 .
